Operations at the Manatial Espejo, COSE and Joaquin mines, in Santa Cruz, Argentina, have been suspended following an employee fatality at the COSE mine, Nasdaq- and TSX-listed Pan American Silver reported on Monday. The employee died in a fall-of-ground incident, the world’s second largest primary silver producer said. “We are deeply saddened by this tragic accident and extend our thoughts and sympathies to the employee's family and co-workers," president and CEO Michael Steinmann said in a media statement. The operations would be restarted in coordination with the authorities and union following a safety assessment.